'''Klinika za plućne bolesti''' (Department of Pulmonary Diseases) is a hospital specializing in lung diseases such as [[tuberculosis]], [[lung cancer]], [[bronchitis]], etc.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ukctuzla.ba/ukctuzla/organizacija?layout=edit&id=2020|title=KLINIKA ZA PLUĆNE BOLESTI|publisher=UKC Tuzla|date=9 January 2015|accessdate=12 April 2015}}</ref> It was opened in 1953 in the Slavinovići neighborhood of [[Tuzla]], [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]]. The hospital was renovated in 2006. [[File:Slavinovici_plaque.jpg|thumb|180px|left|A plaque on the hospital that reads "''This hospital was opened in the year 1953, and whose construction helped the miners of the Uglja, Tito, and [[Banovići]] mines, and the work of others from the Tuzla basin''".]] ==History== After 57 years, the hospital finally had heating installed in autumn 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tuzla.danas.info/2010/09/28/klinika-za-plucne-bolesti-i-tuberkulozu-prikljucena-na-daljinsko-grijanje/|title=Klinika za plućne bolesti i tuberkulozu priključena na daljinsko grijanje|publisher=Tuzla danas|date=28 September 2010|accessdate=12 April 2015}}</ref>
