'''Derzelas''' (''Darzalas'') was a [[Dacia]]n or [[Thracians|Thracian]] [[chthonic]] god of abundance and the underworld, health and human spirit's vitality.<ref>{{cite journal|last=Gočeva|first=Zlatozara|title=Organization of Religious Life in Odessos|journal=Kernos|year=1996|volume=9|pages=121–127}}</ref>
Darzalas was the god of [[Hellenistic period]] Odessos (modern [[Varna]]) and was frequently depicted on its [http://www.wildwinds.com/coins/greece/thrace/odessos/ coinage] from the third century BCE to the third century CE<ref>{{cite book|author1=C. J. Howgego |author2=Volker Heuchert |author3=Andrew M. Burnett |title=Coinage and Identity in the Roman Provinces|year=2008|publisher=Oxford University Press|isbn=9780199237845|page=110}}</ref> and portrayed in numerous [[terracotta]] figurines, as well as in a rare 4th century BC lead one ([http://www.varna-bg.com/museums/archaeology/pictures/musexibit/darsalas.jpg photo]), found in the city. Darzalas was often depicted in [[himation]], holding [[cornucopia]]e with [[altar]]s by his side. There was a temple dedicated to him with a cult statue, and games (''Darzaleia'') were held in his honor every five years, possibly attended by [[Gordian III]] in 238 CE.
Another temple dedicated to Derzelas was built at [[Histria (ancient city)|Histria]] - a [[Colonies in antiquity#Greek colonies|Greek colony]] on the shore of the [[Black Sea]] in the third century BC.
[[Darzalas Peak]] on [[Trinity Peninsula]] in [[Antarctica]] is named after the god.<ref>[http://data.aad.gov.au/aadc/gaz/scar/ SCAR Composite Gazetteer of Antarctica] {{webarchive|url=https://www.webcitation.org/5ug2CfC7m?url=http://data.aad.gov.au/aadc/gaz/scar/ |date=2010-12-02 }}</ref>{{citation needed|reason=not specified|date=June 2016}}
