{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2015}} {{Use British English|date=October 2015}} {{Infobox company | name = Veolia Water East | logo = Veolia Water.png | logo_size = 200px | caption = | type = Subsidiary | traded_as = | fate = | predecessor = Tendring Hundred Water | successor = | foundation = 1989<!-- {{Start date|df=yes|1989|MM|DD}} --> | founder = | defunct = <!-- {{End date|df=yes|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | location_city = | location_country = | location = Mill Hill, Manningtree, CO11 2AZ, United Kingdom | locations = | area_served = [[Tendring District|Tendring]] peninsula | key_people = | industry = [[Water supply]], [[water treatment]] and [[sewage treatment]] | products = | services = | revenue = | operating_income = | net_income = | aum = <!-- Only used with financial services companies --> | assets = | equity = | owner = | num_employees = | parent = [[Veolia Environnement]] (through Veolia Water) | divisions = | subsid = | homepage = {{URL|https://east.veoliawater.co.uk/|east.veoliawater.co.uk}} | footnotes = | intl = }} [[File:Kortill Vanster - geograph.org.uk - 126160.jpg|thumb|The company's main treatment works are on the right]] '''Veolia Water East''', formerly known as '''Tendring Hundred Water Services''', was a privately owned company supplying water to the [[Tendring District|Tendring]] peninsula in north east [[Essex]] within an area of {{Convert|352|km2|sqmi}}. In July 2009, the company, a subsidiary of [[Veolia Water]] UK since 1989, part of [[Veolia Environment]], changed its name from Tendring Hundred Water.
In 2012, following the sale of Veolia Water's UK water supply business, it was merged with [[Veolia Water Southeast]] and [[Veolia Water Central]] to form [[Affinity Water]] on 1 October 2012.
